com.urbancode.ubuild.scripting.wrappers
Class BuildLifeWrapper

java.lang.Object
  com.urbancode.ubuild.scripting.wrappers.WrapperBase
      com.urbancode.ubuild.scripting.wrappers.BuildLifeWrapper

public class BuildLifeWrapper
extends WrapperBase

Scripting class to give limited access to BuildLife information. This is exposed as 'buildLife' in some notification scripts.

Examples:

To get the name of the build life: 

    buildLife.getName()
To get the id of the build life: 
    buildLife.getId()
To get the latest stamp of the build life: 
    buildLife.latestStamp()
To get the latest status of the build life: 
    buildLife.latestStatus()
To get the workflow case for the build life: 
    buildLife.getWorkflow()
To get the previous build life: 
    buildLife.getPrevious()
To get the artifact sets that have been published to for the build life: 
    buildLife.getArtifactSets()
To get the artifacts in an artifact set on a build life: 
    buildLife.getArtifactsForArtifactSet("setName")
To get a list of the change sets published to the build life: 
    buildLife.getChangeSets()
To get a comma-separated list of all of the change paths for all change sets on the build life: 
    buildLife.getChangePaths()
To get a comma-separated list of the internal ids for the change sets published to the build life: 
    buildLife.getChangeSetIds()
To get a comma-separated list of the SCM ids for the change sets published to the build life: 
    buildLife.getChangeSetScmIds()
To get a list of the issues published to the build life: 
    buildLife.getIssues()
To get a comma-separated list of the ids for the issues published to the build life: 
    buildLife.getIssueIds()
To get a list of the coverage reports published to the build life: 
    buildLife.getCoverageReports()
To get a list of the dependency changes for the build life: 
    buildLife.getDependencyChanges()
To get a list of the source analytic reports published to the build life: 
    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports()
To get a list of the test reports published to the build life: 
    buildLife.getTestReports()
To get a link to the build life: 
    buildLife.getUrl()
If you are using velocity scripts for Notification Templates, you don't have to use the full method name for getters: 
    buildLife.Name
    buildLife.Id
    buildLife.Workflow
    buildLife.Previous
    buildLife.ArtifactSets
    buildLife.ChangeSets
    buildLife.ChangePaths
    buildLife.ChangeSetIds
    buildLife.ChangeSetScmIds
    buildLife.Issues
    buildLife.IssueIds
    buildLife.CoverageReports
    buildLife.DependencyChanges
    buildLife.SourceAnalyticReports
    buildLife.TestReports
    buildLife.Url
To display all build life properties in a notification: 
    Build Life Properties:
    #set($buildLifeProperties = $buildLife.properties)
    #foreach($propName in $buildLifeProperties.keySet())
        $propName: $buildLifeProperties.get($propName)
    #end
If you are trying to retrieve some build life properties in a process, you would prefix the property with 'buildlife/' For example, to get the latest stamp value for a build life: 
    ${p:buildlife/latestStamp}
To get the latest status for a build life: 
    ${p:buildlife/latestStatus}
To get information like the project name from a build life, you might need to chain some of these calls together. First, you would have to get the workflow from the build life, followed by the project from the workflow, etc. For example: 
    ${p:buildlife/workflow/project/name}
To get a specific property name 'specific.property' on the build life: 
    ${p:buildlife/properties[@name='specific.property'}
To get a list of the external issue ids for use within a job step: 
    ${p:buildlife/issueIds}
To get all property values based on the property name, you can use the functions startsWith, contains and matches: 
    ${p:fn:startsWith(buildlife/properties, 'prefix')}
    ${p:fn:contains(buildlife/properties, 'text')}
    ${p:fn:matches(buildlife/properties, 'prefix.*')}
